This rib re-expresses the OSDU CIMPL "bridge" as a Keelson rib. It bundles none
of the OSDU toolchain: its collectors shell the community CLIs below (installed
by the operator on PATH) and shape their JSON output into generic, domain-free
Keelson canvas views. Attribution to the upstream projects whose tooling and
vision this rib builds on follows.

==============================================================================
CIMPL Stack — the `cimpl` CLI (cluster bootstrap + Flux GitOps for OSDU)
==============================================================================

The Cluster and topology surfaces shell the `cimpl` CLI (`cimpl info`,
`cimpl reconcile`, `cimpl down`) and read the Flux state it provisions. The
rib's cluster/topology shaping re-expresses the OSDU CIMPL bridge; its dashboard
composer logic is near-ported (ported, never imported).

  Project:  CIMPL Stack
  Source:   https://community.opengroup.org/osdu/platform/deployment-and-operations/cimpl-stack
  License:  Apache License 2.0 (https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0)

==============================================================================
AI DevOps Agent — the `osdu-activity` and `osdu-quality` CLIs
==============================================================================

The Quality, Features, and Security lanes shell the OSDU AI DevOps Agent CLIs
(`osdu-quality release`, `osdu-activity epic`/`mr`) and shape their JSON output
into boards.

  Project:  AI DevOps Agent (OSDU Community Utilities)
  Source:   https://community.opengroup.org/osdu/ui/ai-devops-agent/community
  License:  Apache License 2.0 (https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0)
